1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,922
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:12,303
‪[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:17,809
[Martina, in English] <i>Who is that?</i>

4
00:00:17,892 --> 00:00:19,936
[Red] <i>The old person who caused trouble</i>
<i>at Endless Nights last night.</i>

5
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,354
[Martina] <i>Military?</i>

6
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:23,356
[Red] <i>That is what I am asking</i>
<i>my people to find out.</i>

7
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:25,275
<i>I need to find out where he is connected.</i>

8
00:00:25,358 --> 00:00:27,819
[Ame] Maybe we should
just go back to Atoy’s house.

9
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:28,987
We can eat there.

10
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,363
[Atoy] <i>Ibyang!</i>

11
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:31,531
PREVIOUSLY

12
00:00:31,614 --> 00:00:34,117
[Ame] <i>Why are you smiling there?</i>

13
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,452
<i>You miss Atoy, right?</i>

14
00:00:36,578 --> 00:00:38,705
Why would I miss that grumpy one?

15
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:40,957
[men grunting and groaning]

16
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:43,251
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

17
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:45,962
[Atoy] <i>There is a room there.</i>
<i>No one is using it.</i>

18
00:00:46,045 --> 00:00:47,297
You can use it!

19
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:48,840
[Cita] <i>Come on to your new room.</i>

20
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:49,966
<i>He might change his mind. Come on now!</i>

21
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,676
[Delfin] <i>I want you to have</i>

22
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,554
<i>what we had</i>
<i>when your mother was still alive.</i>

23
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:57,515
<i>Have your own family</i>

24
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:00,518
<i>who will love you</i>

25
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,437
<i>and whom you will love.</i>

26
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,773
- [Dmitri, in English] <i>Welcome home, child.</i>
- [Audrey, in English] <i>Thanks, Dad.</i>

27
00:01:05,648 --> 00:01:06,691
[in English] Welcome back, sis!

28
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:07,942
[Martina, in English] <i>Vacation, or what?</i>

29
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:08,902
[in English] For good?

30
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:09,819
[in English] We will see.

31
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,488
[both chuckle sarcastically]

32
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,616
[Dmitri, in English] Come on,
let us go inside. Everyone.

33
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:16,743
[Dmitri sighs]

34
00:01:16,826 --> 00:01:19,120
- [girls] Hey!
- [Tonet] Wow, a feast!

35
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:20,330
- [Karla] There is so much food!
- [Ibyang gasps]

36
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:23,124
Is it like this every day here, Ms. Cita?

37
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:24,918
Not really, Sis Ame!

38
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,211
[playful music playing]

39
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:27,712
Who has a birthday?

40
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,088
No one has a birthday.

41
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:31,508
Brother Atoy just asked
for food to be bought.

42
00:01:32,091 --> 00:01:34,886
- Hey, hey!
- Bro, eat, come on!

43
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:37,388
They are happy with your treat!

44
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:38,431
Not really.

45
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:43,019
The card just had extra points.
It would be a waste if they expired.

46
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:45,355
And besides, there is

47
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:48,900
one starving little mouse here.

48
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:50,985
- [Karla] Oh, my.
- [girls chuckle]

49
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:52,904
I am not greedy.

50
00:01:52,987 --> 00:01:54,447
I just eat enthusiastically!

51
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:57,659
Oh, really? Is that
what your chubby cheeks say?!

52
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:59,285
- [Atoy chuckles]
- [Ame] Uh, Atoy,

53
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:00,870
eat here already.

54
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:05,625
Ah! Atoy, sit here now. Here.

55
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,335
[funky music playing]

56
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:09,671
Atoy, what do you prefer with the noodles?

57
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:12,132
More noodles or more vegetables?

58
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:14,843
And for the chicken,
what do you want, Atoy?

59
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:16,761
The white meat or the dark meat?

60
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:20,932
[funky music continues]

61
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:22,642
[both] Atoy!

62
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:23,560
No, thank you.

63
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:26,646
Um, I am already full.

64
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:28,773
You all just eat instead.

65
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:31,192
Just seeing you eat
already makes me happy.

66
00:02:33,236 --> 00:02:35,613
[Ibyang] The food might run out soon.

67
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:37,824
Eat now.

68
00:02:38,366 --> 00:02:39,492
[mischievous music playing]

69
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:40,660
[Ame scoffs]

70
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:57,886
‪[Atoy hums]

71
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:05,768
[sentimental music playing]

72
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:07,854
We are so quiet, right?

73
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:11,316
Because there are only two of us
sitting at the table.

74
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,822
Maybe that is okay too, Dad.

75
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:20,241
Rather than being many of us,

76
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:23,369
it ends up turning into chatter,

77
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,121
and the food ends up being made to wait.

78
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:27,373
As they say in church, right,

79
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,876
grace should not be kept waiting.

80
00:03:30,501 --> 00:03:32,629
We are not really making it wait.

81
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:36,382
Just savor it and enjoy it.

82
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:38,259
You know,

83
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,720
it would probably be nice

84
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:45,183
if many of us were eating together, right?

85
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:46,809
[Atoy] Mmm…

86
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:50,730
That was one
of your mother’s regrets before.

87
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:54,943
We were afraid to have many children.

88
00:03:56,694 --> 00:03:57,695
You know,

89
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:01,241
it would be so joyful

90
00:04:01,866 --> 00:04:03,368
if many of us were…

91
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:07,330
in front of the table,
sharing a meal together.

92
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,709
[sentimental music continues]

93
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:12,669
[clicking]

94
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,087
[Tonet] <i>Ah, Atoy,</i>

95
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,546
<i>sit here now.</i>

96
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,049
[Cita] Atoy, come on, join us and eat.

97
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,134
Oh!

98
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:21,135
You were already told to join in!

99
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:22,971
Come on, come on. Sit here now.

100
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,138
- Come on.
- [Atoy] All right.

101
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:25,348
- Sit down now. Go on.
- [Atoy] Oh.

102
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:26,683
[Atoy clears throat]

103
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,352
- [Atoy groans]
- [Cita] There.

104
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,354
[Atoy] Thank you, Ame.

105
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:33,189
- [Tonet] Here.
- Here, calamansi.

106
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:34,941
- [Ame] Add calamansi so it tastes better.
- Hmm.

107
00:04:35,024 --> 00:04:36,776
- Hey.
- [Cita] Hey.

108
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:37,944
- [Cita] Can you finish that?
- [Ame] Wait, wait.

109
00:04:38,027 --> 00:04:39,404
- Hey, hey!
- [Ame] Here, calamansi.

110
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:40,697
- [suave music playing]
- [muttering]

111
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,198
- [Atoy] Hey.
- [Tonet] Hey.

112
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:43,116
‪[suave music playing]

113
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:11,519
[in English] So, Martina, what is
this project you are working on?

114
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:13,271
[Martina, in English]
It is a surprise, Dad.

115
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:15,356
Um, it is a non-profit thing.

116
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:18,776
[in English] Kind of like a way for Red
and I to give back to the community.

117
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:21,779
And the new building will also
be finished, and as you know,

118
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:23,448
you are invited to the ribbon cutting.

119
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:25,742
[in English] So, like
a new business venture?

120
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:29,162
[in English] Like I said, non-profit.

121
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:30,788
[in English] There is no such thing
as a free lunch.

122
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:31,706
[unsettling music playing]

123
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:33,916
[in English] There is always
a hidden cost somewhere.

124
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:36,919
Can you just be supportive of my spouse?

125
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:38,713
[Martina] Yes, you know…

126
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:42,550
you are so invested. I am thinking like…

127
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:46,345
is my sister-in-law
already interested in our lives?

128
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:48,139
[in English] Of course,

129
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:49,974
[in English] I mean, after all, you are…

130
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:51,350
family.

131
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:53,227
[chuckles softly]

132
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:57,482
Speaking of family,
how is my favorite nephew, Gavin?

133
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,985
[in English] Well, it's still vacation
time, so he is probably just with friends.

134
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:04,489
Would you like me to call him to let
him know that his favorite aunt is here?

135
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:05,406
[in English] No, it's okay.

136
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,574
I'll just see him later.

137
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:09,827
Will you be staying longer this time?

138
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,788
[unsettling music playing]

139
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:14,373
[in English] Well, I want her to.

140
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:16,834
[in English] Dad.

141
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:19,837
[in English] You know I already
have a life in the States.

142
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:23,716
But your family
is here in the Philippines.

143
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,717
[music intensifies]

144
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:25,843
[Martina, in English]
You know, Dad is right.

145
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:28,137
There are only
a few of us left in the family.

146
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:29,472
Will we still separate?

147
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:32,100
[in English] Come on, Sis Martina.

148
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:36,229
We all know that you and your spouse
prefer that I am abroad.

149
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:39,982
[sniffs]

150
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:40,942
[Red] What is your problem?

151
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:43,778
You just arrived, and you
are already starting fights.

152
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:44,695
You keep making remarks!

153
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:45,613
[unsettling music playing]

154
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:46,614
Red.

155
00:06:48,157 --> 00:06:49,492
[in English] I need some air.

156
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,619
After all these years,

157
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,539
it still feels suffocating in this house.

158
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,041
[in English] Excuse me, Dad.

159
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:58,709
Audrey.

160
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:02,922
[pensive music playing]

161
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:06,050
Why did she even come back,
if she does not even want to be here?

162
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:09,137
Because I forced her.

163
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,430
[pensive music continues]

164
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,723
[in English] I am not
getting any younger, Red.

165
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,394
I am also getting tired of going
back and forth to America

166
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:17,812
just to see your sister.

167
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:20,565
[in English] So please,

168
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:25,862
don't do anything
that would make her leave again.

169
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:27,905
[in English] We will do our best, Dad.

170
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:29,073
[in English] Right?

171
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:31,909
[in English] Yeah.

172
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:36,456
[music intensifies]

173
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:42,795
Aunt Audrey!

174
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,755
Gavin!

175
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,756
[Audrey] Hi!

176
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,924
When did you arrive?

177
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:48,718
Why did you not ask
to be picked up at the airport?

178
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:50,094
What are you saying,
the airport is very close!

179
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:51,762
I do not want to hassle anyone.

180
00:07:51,846 --> 00:07:54,515
Oh, Grandpa, is he with you as well?

181
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,976
He is inside, with your mom and dad.

182
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:00,354
How are you?

183
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,522
You are so handsome!

184
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,441
I am okay. Just chilling.

185
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:04,775
It is our vacation.

186
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:06,486
[in English] I met a girl.

187
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:08,905
[in English] Ooh, is she as pretty as me?

188
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:09,989
[Gavin blows raspberry]

189
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,617
No one compares to you, Auntie.

190
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,993
[in English] Good answer.

191
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:16,746
[in English] But yes, she is pretty.

192
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,080
[Audrey] Hmm…

193
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:20,041
Has she already met your parents?

194
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,001
Not yet, Auntie.

195
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,377
You know Mommy.

196
00:08:23,461 --> 00:08:25,171
She does not want me
to have a girlfriend yet.

197
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,381
You know…

198
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:28,591
I also met someone.

199
00:08:29,091 --> 00:08:30,259
[in English] A few years ago.

200
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:33,387
I was also not able
to introduce him to Dad.

201
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:34,722
[in English] Why?

202
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:36,098
[in English] What happened?

203
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:40,311
[Atoy] This is important to me.

204
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,271
I will come back to this.

205
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:43,606
I will come back for you.

206
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,483
[Atoy] <i>I will explain everything to you.</i>

207
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:52,073
[gentle music playing]

208
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:01,958
I will wait for you,

209
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,293
Mr. Amnesia.

210
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:07,046
[suspenseful music playing]

211
00:09:07,129 --> 00:09:08,130
Who are you?!

212
00:09:09,173 --> 00:09:10,383
Help!

213
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:15,054
[Audrey, muffled grunting]

214
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:16,097
- [Audrey screams]
- [man grunts]

215
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:18,766
[grunting]

216
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:22,770
- [thuds]
- [Audrey grunts]

217
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:26,315
[in English] Fate… happened.

218
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:29,527
I never saw him again.

219
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:34,240
[in English] So, don't let that happen
between you and this girl.

220
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:35,449
[gentle music playing]

221
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:36,450
By the way, what is her name?

222
00:09:40,454 --> 00:09:42,373
Master eats so fast.

223
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,041
Is Master on a diet?

224
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,252
Oh, dear,

225
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:49,463
he might have been put off.

226
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:53,926
How could he not? Earlier,
someone kept sticking close to him.

227
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,595
[quirky music playing]

228
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:57,305
Atoy left

229
00:09:57,388 --> 00:10:02,059
because someone there
almost tried to feed him her food.

230
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,811
Acting like a partner!

231
00:10:03,894 --> 00:10:07,523
Hey! Before your banter goes too far,

232
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:11,444
when Brother Atoy is busy,
he barely eats at all.

233
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:13,237
[Karla] You talk too much.

234
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:14,864
[music concludes]

235
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:17,366
What is Master busy with?

236
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:19,201
Is it still the rooster?

237
00:10:19,827 --> 00:10:20,745
- What rooster?
- [pensive music playing]

238
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:24,332
Before Master found Sis Ame,

239
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:30,338
someone asked Master to find a rooster
for one of his customers.

240
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:32,673
What kind of rooster?

241
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:35,843
Is it the kind that lays golden eggs?

242
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:39,096
Golden eggs?

243
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,848
- Do those exist?
- [Tonet] Mmm-hmm!

244
00:10:40,931 --> 00:10:42,433
In fairy tales!

245
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,976
Is that what he was looking for?

246
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:45,478
[Ibyang] No.

247
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:50,566
It seems like a fighting rooster.
That was what he was asked to find.

248
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:52,860
A fighting rooster?

249
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:59,867
[pensive music playing]

250
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:02,662
I have already spoken to our contacts
at the cockfighting ring, sir.

251
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:03,579
They said

252
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:05,498
<i>that what we are looking for</i>

253
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,291
<i>has not shown up at the derby yet at all.</i>

254
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:08,250
So,

255
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:11,504
either they are still looking
for the right fight…

256
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:15,049
Or they really have
no intention of fighting it.

257
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,593
Because, sir, its record is excellent.

258
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:20,596
It really seems fitting
to be used as a stud.

259
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:22,473
Or…

260
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:26,727
maybe they already turned it into tinola
and ate it as beer bites.

261
00:11:26,811 --> 00:11:28,521
[chuckles]

262
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:31,315
If that is the case, it looks like

263
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:34,402
it would need to be boiled
for a long time to become tender.

264
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:37,947
[chuckles]

265
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:38,864
It is fine, sir.

266
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:41,951
Once I have a new lead, I will inform you.

267
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:43,994
[in English] Good luck, Padua.

268
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,538
Okay, sir.

269
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:49,917
[knocking on door]

270
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:53,671
- Who is that?
- [Ame] Atoy, it is Ame.

271
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:05,558
[charming music playing]

272
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,894
[in English] I am here for you, Ame.

273
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,647
Whatever you need,

274
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:14,275
I will give it.

275
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,528
[Atoy] Ame, what is it?

276
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:19,655
What do you need?

277
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:21,157
[playful music playing]

278
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,241
[Atoy] Hey!

279
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,371
Ame, what do you need?

280
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:30,082
Is Ibyang pestering you again?

281
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,208
Ah, no.

282
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:33,252
I just wanted to tell you

283
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:36,630
that it seems I know
where the rooster you are looking for is.

284
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:38,716
[pensive music playing]

285
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:39,675
Ame.

286
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:43,387
The kind of rooster
I am looking for is different.

287
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:44,847
It is not just any rooster.

288
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:47,183
What has Ibyang been telling you?

289
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,642
- Just joking--
- The breed of the rooster

290
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,352
you are looking for is Kelso, right?

291
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:52,646
Yes.

292
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:56,358
Does the rooster you are
looking for also have a name?

293
00:12:57,109 --> 00:13:00,029
Because from what I heard,

294
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:01,780
it does.

295
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:05,242
Um… Draco.

296
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,286
That is the name.

297
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:11,916
What was the name again
of the rooster you mentioned?

298
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:14,335
[Ame] Draco.

299
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:18,005
[tense music playing]

300
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:18,923
Draco.

301
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:24,261
Where did you hear that?

302
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,430
At the bar,

303
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:28,349
when I was still locked up there.

304
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:34,230
[tense music continues]

305
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:35,147
[man 1] Come in!

306
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:38,609
Hurry up and pee already!

307
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:39,860
[man 2] Hey! Hurry up!

308
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,028
[man 1] Here it is!

309
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:43,280
This is really clear. Looks great.

310
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:44,490
Nice.

311
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,076
With the new cellphone,
looks like you are rich!

312
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:49,995
Yes, I had a side job!

313
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:53,791
I was hired by one of our regulars
to steal a rooster.

314
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,709
[man 1] How much?

315
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,836
- [man 2] Fifty thousand!
- [man 1] Seriously?!

316
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:01,674
[man 2] Yes!
Because the breed is imported, Kelso.

317
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:02,841
And it is intense,

318
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:05,678
always winning at the derby!

319
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:06,804
Impressive!

320
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,180
Yes! Hardcore!

321
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:10,015
[man 2] The owner did not want to sell it.

322
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:11,809
So, they just had it stolen.

323
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:14,228
That is crazy, bro!

324
00:14:14,311 --> 00:14:15,145
Why?

325
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,231
The rooster even has a name!

326
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:19,108
- [man 1] Huh?
- [man 2] Yes!

327
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:21,944
[man 2] Ah… Draco. Draco, bro.

328
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,070
[man 1] Who is that customer?

329
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:25,281
Maybe I can come along to earn too.

330
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,907
[man 2] It is Boss Chipper.

331
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:28,367
[man 1] Chipper?

332
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:30,077
[in English] As in Chipper Arenas?

333
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,954
[man 2] Exactly, bro! Exactly!

334
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:34,290
[in English] Chipper? As in…

335
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,542
[in English] As in Chipper Arenas?

336
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:38,586
Yes, that is him!

337
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,462
[music intensifies]

338
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:41,422
Oh.

339
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,675
[scoffs]

340
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:48,554
[in English] Thank you, thank you!
Thank you! [grunts]

341
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:49,638
[elated huff]

342
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:50,681
[Ame cooing]

343
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:54,810
[in English] Love you too.

344
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:59,440
- [door clicks shut]
- [mischievous music playing]

345
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,112
Yes, Chipper Arenas.

346
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:06,572
He is a cockfighter.

347
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,658
And if there is
no address that we can get,

348
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:12,620
even just the place
where they fight, that will do.

349
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:14,830
[pensive music playing]

350
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,458
All right, Bok, just inform me
when you have something, okay?

351
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:19,668
Thank you.

352
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,794
Atoy.

353
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,546
- [Atoy] Oh.
- Can I talk to you?

354
00:15:23,547 --> 00:15:24,715
Of course. What is it?

355
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:26,592
Atoy!

356
00:15:26,675 --> 00:15:28,010
Ah!

357
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:30,012
Maybe later instead.

358
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:32,306
[mischievous music playing]

359
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:33,432
Atoy!

360
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,768
Oh?

361
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:37,603
Emerson.

362
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,314
The shop is closing.
Just come back tomorrow.

363
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:41,899
- What is it?
- I heard that you are

364
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:45,069
now accepting boarders here.

365
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:46,862
- [scoffs]
- [mischievous music playing]

366
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:49,490
News really spreads fast
here in Tabang Lupa, huh?

367
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,450
Or are you just really nosy?

368
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:52,910
[scoffs]

369
00:15:52,993 --> 00:15:55,537
Atoy, I am concerned about the community.

370
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,289
[Emerson scoffs]

371
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,625
You are taking in two young girls.

372
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:01,627
Did you do a background check on them?

373
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:05,172
Maybe you are letting criminals
stay here in our area.

374
00:16:05,255 --> 00:16:07,091
[scoffs] You are unbelievable, Emerson!

375
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:09,718
You even think of children that way?

376
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:10,678
What is going on with you?

377
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:12,388
[mischievous music continues]

378
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,683
Emerson, do not be
too invested in my life.

379
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:18,852
People around here might start thinking

380
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,104
that you have a crush on me.

381
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:21,522
- Wow!
- [chuckles]

382
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:24,149
[in English] Atoy,
"stuff" making "fund" of me, huh!

383
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,819
What crush? What do you think I am, gay?

384
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:28,487
- [Atoy, in English] Good night!
- I am not gay!

385
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:29,822
[funky music playing]

386
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:30,906
Who said I am gay?

387
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:33,659
Huh? Who said I am gay?

388
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:35,119
Who?

389
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,620
Who?

390
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,164
[Atoy] Psst! Hey!
What are you peeking at there?

391
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:40,708
Seriously, sir!

392
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:43,002
Atoy, come on! You are startling me!

393
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,087
Sorry, because, uh…
What are you doing there?

394
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,130
Why are you hiding?

395
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,923
- Huh? Nothing.
- Huh?

396
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,299
Nothing. Nothing.

397
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:50,217
What do you mean nothing?

398
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:52,052
Earlier when you went out,

399
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:54,138
you suddenly avoided Emerson.

400
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,432
And now you are hiding and peeking.

401
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,726
What? Why, did he harass you?

402
00:16:58,809 --> 00:16:59,935
What… Did he do something to you?

403
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:01,186
No, not like that.

404
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,396
Nothing like that, I promise.

405
00:17:02,479 --> 00:17:04,148
- Oh, then what?
- What, uh…

406
00:17:05,482 --> 00:17:09,028
Uh, he looks like…
He looks like my former suitor.

407
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,404
That is why I do not want to see him.

408
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:12,197
That would be bad.

409
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:14,616
Ah, well, if you say so.

410
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:17,036
So, uh, what was it again?

411
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,704
What were you asking me earlier?

412
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:21,248
Ah…

413
00:17:21,331 --> 00:17:22,291
Well,

414
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:25,002
I just wanted to ask about the rooster.

415
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:27,296
Did Ame help you?

416
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,465
Ame, yes!

417
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,050
Ame was a huge help to me.

418
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,676
Oh, really?

419
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:34,511
Me,

420
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:35,637
I can also help you.

421
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,097
I am just here. You have no--

422
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:37,973
[claps]

423
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,767
If you need someone
to do makeup for you again…

424
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:40,684
[chuckles]

425
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:41,727
I am at your service.

426
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:42,770
[inhales]

427
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:47,191
I know your outside work is important, so…

428
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:49,276
You can count on me. I promise!

429
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:50,194
I will keep quiet.

430
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:52,529
- Really?
- [Tonet] Yes.

431
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:56,408
[funky music playing]

432
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:57,659
Oh, then,

433
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,536
you are now my official
makeup artist from now on.

434
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,871
- Is that okay?
- Really?!

435
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:02,039
[shrieks] Oh! Oh!

436
00:18:02,122 --> 00:18:04,249
Thank you so much!

437
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:08,170
[Tonet, muffled chuckles]

438
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,713
- [phone ringing]
- Ah, wait.

439
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:11,882
[Tonet] Oh, oh, sorry.

440
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:13,550
[shy chuckle] Sorry.

441
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:14,468
Hello, bro.

442
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:16,136
Yes.

443
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,554
[mischievous music playing]

444
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:18,597
[Atoy] Chipper Arenas.

445
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,765
Yes, that is him.

446
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,354
Yes, where he can be found.

447
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:30,234
[tense music playing]

448
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:34,196
[sinister music playing]

449
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:36,907
Has Draco already mated with many hens?

450
00:18:37,407 --> 00:18:38,826
- Quite a few already, boss.
- [cock crowing]

451
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:40,577
Some are already laying eggs.

452
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,204
[in English] Good.

453
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:43,914
[rooster crowing]

454
00:18:43,997 --> 00:18:45,541
There is already a buyer for Draco.

455
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:49,044
So, we need to maximize
their vacation here on the farm.

456
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,088
- [chuckles]
- [roosters clucking]

457
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:54,716
BAYANET
SURELY CONNECTED

458
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,468
[tense music playing]

459
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:06,854
It turns out there are many roosters
belonging to Chipper.

460
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,026
[in English] Two roving guards,

461
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,113
with a sidearm.

462
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,991
[tense music continues]

463
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:44,141
[guard] All right, park it at the back.

464
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:47,144
So, did you give everything away?

465
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:48,937
[woman] Some are left.

466
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:51,899
Because some houses
did not have anyone inside.

467
00:19:52,399 --> 00:19:53,567
[tutting]

468
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:54,651
[guard] Just leave it.

469
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:59,364
[tense music continues]

470
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:03,243
Oh, my!

471
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:10,459
[Atoy] Oh, my goodness!

472
00:20:11,627 --> 00:20:13,503
Sorry about this, because my boss
will make me pay for this.

473
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:15,130
[Atoy chuckles]

474
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:17,674
[Atoy clicks tongue]

475
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:18,800
[Atoy] Seriously!

476
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:20,385
Whoo!

477
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:24,181
[Atoy] This is intense, really.

478
00:20:24,681 --> 00:20:25,599
Huh.

479
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,102
Oh, my goodness.

480
00:20:29,811 --> 00:20:35,025
[thrilling music continues]

481
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:42,699
[music concludes]

482
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,451
[Ame] Ibyang, there is more.

483
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:45,661
- [Ame] Ibyang, there is more underneath.
- [Cita] What time is it already?

484
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:47,704
[Cita] Oh, no,
I still need to cook at home!

485
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,623
- Stay here for now, Tonet.
- Ah.

486
00:20:49,706 --> 00:20:50,999
- [Tonet] Oh!
- I will continue that later.

487
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,626
- [Cita] Oh? I am leaving now.
- All right, Ms. Cita.

488
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:53,919
- I am fine staying here.
- [Cita] Okay, okay, okay.

489
00:20:54,002 --> 00:20:55,420
- [Cita] I will go ahead.
- Yes.

490
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:58,382
All right then, Ibyang,

491
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,549
that is enough.

492
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:01,510
Ah, Ibyang.

493
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:04,054
- [Ibyang] Hmm.
- Check the rice first,

494
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:06,890
then unplug the rice cooker
if it is cooked, okay?

495
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:10,477
Uh, once it is cooked, can we eat already?

496
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:12,896
Just make sure you leave
some viand for Atoy.

497
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,314
[funky music playing]

498
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:16,942
They are quite stingy with viand.

499
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:20,821
I will just leave one piece of adobo.

500
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:22,698
[Ame and Ibyang chuckle]

501
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:28,829
Ah, A-Ame.

502
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:31,290
Can I talk to you?

503
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:35,544
Actually, I also want to talk to you.
That is why I sent Ibyang away.

504
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,254
[mischievous music playing]

505
00:21:37,337 --> 00:21:38,505
You know,

506
00:21:39,756 --> 00:21:41,758
I am feeling some vibes from you.

507
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:44,720
I just want to confirm my suspicion.

508
00:21:46,888 --> 00:21:48,640
- Do you like Atoy?
- You like Atoy.

509
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:50,392
[mischievous music continues]

510
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:51,560
[gasps]

511
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:58,817
[mysterious music playing]

512
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:01,945
[woman, in English] <i>Good day,</i>
<i>magic on your way!</i>

513
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:03,655
<i>How can we help you today?</i>

514
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:07,409
[in English] Hello.
This is, uh, Mr. Arenas.

515
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,787
[in English] I booked you
for this coming Saturday, right?

516
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:12,497
[woman, in English] <i>Yes, sir,</i>
<i>that is correct.</i>

517
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:16,251
[in English] Well, uh,
I would like to cancel, uh, my booking.

518
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:17,961
That is allowed, right?

519
00:22:18,545 --> 00:22:20,297
[woman] <i>That is allowed, sir, but</i>

520
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,799
<i>we have a policy that if you cancel,</i>

521
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:25,469
- <i>the down payment will not be refunded.</i>
- [scoffs]

522
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:27,262
[in English] That is all right,
that is all right.

523
00:22:27,345 --> 00:22:29,848
The child changed his mind.

524
00:22:29,931 --> 00:22:33,268
[chuckles] He does not
want to see a magician.

525
00:22:33,351 --> 00:22:34,519
[woman, in English] <i>Noted, sir.</i>

526
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:37,397
[in English] Okay, maybe next time.

527
00:22:37,481 --> 00:22:39,941
[woman, in English] <i>Okay, Mr. Arenas.</i>
<i>Have a good day.</i>

528
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:43,236
[mysterious music continues]

529
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,463
[tense music playing]

530
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,007
My person has never failed.

531
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:06,051
[in English] You will get your Draco,

532
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:07,010
whatever the cost.

533
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:08,470
[Dmitri, in English]
<i>I would like to meet him.</i>

534
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:09,805
[Atoy, in English] Bingo!

535
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:12,724
- Hey, hey, hey!
- [rooster clucking]

536
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:14,768
[guard grunting]

537
00:23:14,851 --> 00:23:15,727
- [loud crack]
- [Tonet] Hey, what was that?

538
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:16,686
Maybe just a rat.

539
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,271
- [Ibyang] Bah!
- [Karla] Ibyang?

540
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:19,439
[in English] The one and only!

541
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:22,692
[Karla] <i>If Brother Atoy sees you,</i>
<i>you are really in trouble.</i>

542
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:23,610
Have they been seen already?!

543
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:25,403
[guards] <i>All our roving guards</i>
<i>are moving, boss.</i>

544
00:23:25,487 --> 00:23:27,781
[Chipper] Just make sure
they cannot get out!

545
00:23:27,864 --> 00:23:29,116
UP NEXT

546
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:30,534
[guard] Sir, sir, sir!

547
00:23:31,368 --> 00:23:32,202
Boss!

548
00:23:32,285 --> 00:23:34,329
[intense music continues]

549
00:23:34,412 --> 00:23:35,247
What is that in your mouth?

550
00:23:39,709 --> 00:23:42,796
Subtitle translation by: Judy Galleta
